  "body": "### Environment information\r\n\r\n* `brownie` Version: 1.17.0\r\n* `ganache-cli` Version: 6.12.2 (core v2.13.2)\r\n* ~`solc` Version: x.x.x~\r\n* Python Version: 3.7.6\r\n* OS: macos\r\n\r\n### What was wrong?\r\n\r\nwhen introducing a new `Contract()` to brownie when having `autofetch_source: True`, it runs a `from_explorer` and gets necessary abi. however, if that contract happens to be a proxy, brownie is never aware of any changes to the implementation contract.\r\n\r\nin other words, if in the next implementation of the contract the signature of the contract changes (eg a new func is introduced), brownie never becomes aware, and will raise a\r\n> AttributeError: Contract 'SomeProxyContract' object has not attribute 'newFunc'\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nPointers to possible solutions or responsible code are welcome :)",
